# Phase 32: Background Image Settings Implementation

I have fully implemented the expanded background image settings feature according to your approved plan.

## Overview of Changes

> [!NOTE]
> Background images across Song, Scripture, and Blank screens now fully support the same dynamic Layout (Stretch/Keep Aspect Ratio) and Alignment choices as standard image slides!

### 1. Database and Provider Upgrades
- Safely extended the `PresentationSettings` Isar schema to store six new persistent properties:
  - `songBackgroundImageLayout`, `songBackgroundImageAlignment`
  - `scriptureBackgroundImageLayout`, `scriptureBackgroundImageAlignment`
  - `blankBackgroundImageLayout`, `blankBackgroundImageAlignment`
- Ran the `build_runner` to synchronize the local database mappings with these new fields.
- Updated the `EditingPresetNotifier` provider to safely update these new values and gracefully fallback to default settings ('stretch' and 'center') for existing presets.

### 2. Streamlined UI Workflow
- Modified the `PresentationSettingsDialog` so that when a user wants to assign a background image, they click a new **'Add'** button instead of a simple 'Browse' file picker.
- This invokes the existing `ImageSlideDialog` with a custom presentation (Title: "Background Image Settings", Submit: "Done").
- When a user previously selected an image, its path, layout, and alignment choices will elegantly pre-populate this dialog so that it acts like an editor instead of starting fresh.

### 3. Rendering Engine Integration
- Re-wired the `ProjectorView` layer logic. The background layer now smartly translates the newly saved Layout and Alignment strings.
- Instead of being hardcoded to `BoxFit.cover` (which forcefully stretched and cropped), it explicitly respects:
  - **'Stretch'**: Expands the image to occupy all pixel real estate (`BoxFit.fill`).
  - **'Keep Aspect Ratio'**: Adjusts to bounds proportionally (`BoxFit.contain`).
  - **Alignments**: Pinpoint alignment configurations are smoothly parsed directly into the `Image` wrapper.

## Verification
- Code successfully builds and runs.
- `flutter analyze` shows zero new errors or regressions.
- Open your Presentation Settings, hit 'Add' under the Background Image option, tweak the settings, and immediately observe them applied in real-time onto your preview canvas!
